<section><div class="sec-inner">
<span class="lbl">What we'd tell you about this pattern</span>
<h2 class="h2">What worked, what we'd do differently, what this means for your stage</h2>

<h3 class="h3">What worked</h3>
<ul class="ul">
<li><strong>Owning marketing as a long-arc engagement, not a project.</strong> Six years sounds long for a fractional engagement; the multi-year continuity is what made global expansion possible. Marketing leadership that turns over every 18 months loses the operator relationships and channel knowledge that compound.</li>
<li><strong>Vertical-specific positioning over generic.</strong> "Software for boutique and multi-location fitness operators" beats "gym software" in every market we tested. Narrower positioning, broader buyer pool.</li>
<li><strong>Trade show + brand event coordination.</strong> In B2B SaaS targeting operators, in-person industry events still matter materially. Coordinating product launches, brand moments, and partner relationships around major trade shows compresses the GTM clock.</li>
</ul>

<h3 class="h3">What we'd do differently</h3>
<ul class="ul">
<li><strong>Earlier AI-native systems.</strong> The current AI agent infrastructure for lead nurture, no-show recovery, and content production wasn't available in 2017 — but the principles of operator-centric automation were. We'd build that operational layer earlier in a comparable engagement today. See <a href="/ai-native-fractional-cmo" style="color:#00C853;">AI-native fractional CMO</a>.</li>
<li><strong>Faster EMEA + APAC playbook adaptation.</strong> The North American playbook ran for ~2.5 years before serious EMEA adaptation began. With the benefit of hindsight, parallel adaptation 12-18 months earlier would have compressed the global expansion arc.</li>
</ul>

<h3 class="h3">If you're a B2B SaaS company evaluating fractional CMO</h3>
<p class="body">This pattern — fractional Head of Marketing / GTM Strategy as the durable senior leadership through multi-year scale-up — fits B2B SaaS companies that have product-market fit and need to professionalize the commercial motion as they expand into new markets, larger operators, or international geographies. See <a href="/fractional-cmo-b2b-saas" style="color:#00C853;">Fractional CMO for B2B SaaS</a> for the operating model in detail, and <a href="/ai-native-fractional-cmo" style="color:#00C853;">AI-native fractional CMO</a> for how the model has evolved since 2017.</p>
</div></section>

